nd cultural context. The book is aimed primarily at readers at undergraduate level and upwards with an interest in sociology, the sociology of the body, the sociology of sport, gender and the sociology of health and illness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBelonging (Social psychology). 0aLong distance swimming. 0aSportsxSociological aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAquatic sociology.  aEmbodiment.  aHealth.  aIdentity.  aImmersion.  aMarathon swimming.  aSocial worlds.  aSport.1 aThrosby, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610046740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526100467423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526100467/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles